		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hello there,<br /><br />my first post.<br /><br />I have tree french nes... this model is very peculiar... doesn't have RF modulator or composite...  has a customized multi-AV (not compatible with SNES and more recent consoles).<br /><br />her'es the foto<br /><br /><img src="https://s1.postimg.org/13py1ojii7/NES-_FR.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Yes, it says RGB.. but in reality is a composite to some kind of rgb converter... not great quality in image.<br /><br />So, due to this low quality image, and the low avaiability of cables, and the price os the ones i found, i was looking in the web for a mod to extract the composite signal, while maintainning the possibility to use the original cable...<br /><br />So i make this scheamatics, with some improvments over the original scheme...<br /><br /><img src="https://s1.postimg.org/4835u3m9e7/nes_fra_mod.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />I'm looking for your opinions before have it a go !!<br /><br />if your feedback is positive, i'm going for it,...<br /><br />thank you.

		

